post_text:
Friday, December 20, 2019, is the last day of school for the first semester. Students will return on Tuesday, January 7, 2020.

With the reopening of State Road 75 in Advance, several changes will be occurring on January 7, 2020.

Students riding "Granville Wells" AM/morning bus routes will be picked up seven minutes later than they currently are.

Granville Wells Elementary School first morning bell will ring at 7:35 a.m. and the tardy bell will ring at 7:52 a.m.

The GWES North Door will open at 7:25 a.m. for student drop-off.

Western Boone and Thorntown arrival and dismissal times will remain the same. Afternoon bus drop-off times will also remain the same.

Busing and transportation questions should be directed to the transportation department at 765.482.6333. Other scheduling questions related to Granville Wells can be directed to the school office at 765.482.6311.

Have a great weekend!

post_text:
Western Boone suffered a terrible loss this week. Our administrative specialist in charge of payroll and benefits, Lora Thompson, passed away unexpectedly on Tuesday. Lora was a dedicated colleague with WBCCSC for over 20 years. Prior to starting in the admin office in 2015, Lora worked as a paraprofessional and in the front office at Thorntown Elementary. Her passing leaves huge void. Each day, Lora brought a pleasant disposition and willingness to help with any situation. There is no doubt that she loved the Western Boone and Thorntown communities. Above all, those who knew her well know that her family meant the world to her. Please keep all of them in your thoughts and prayers during this very difficult time. A link to her full obituary is provided in the comments.

Lora's passing is difficult for us to fully come to terms with because she was here in the office with us last Friday. However, Western Boone is a special community, and we will pull together to grieve the loss of one of our own and lift her family up in our thoughts and prayers.

Superintendent Rob Ramey
text:

Lora was a dedicated colleague with WBCCSC for over 20 years. Prior to starting in the admin office in 2015, Lora worked as a paraprofessional and in the front office at Thorntown Elementary. Her passing leaves huge void. Each day, Lora brought a pleasant disposition and willingness to help with any situation. There is no doubt that she loved the Western Boone and Thorntown communities. Above all, those who knew her well know that her family meant the world to her. Please keep all of them in your thoughts and prayers during this very difficult time. A link to her full obituary is provided in the comments.

Lora's passing is difficult for us to fully come to terms with because she was here in the office with us last Friday. However, Western Boone is a special community, and we will pull together to grieve the loss of one of our own and lift her family up in our thoughts and prayers.

Superintendent Rob Ramey

December 14, 2018 at 6:34 AM ¬∑

#GiveBooneCounty day 5! Bethany Watson-Manager of Grants & Foundation Relations for Gleaners Food Bank of Indiana Inc. joins students of Western Boone County Community School Corporation's National Honor Society as CFBC presents a grant for $8,000 to support their school food pantry!
The pantry is open one day a month-except for July.
There are 10-12 volunteers each month, serving up to 60 families in one month. Julie Hill of WEBO, who coordinates everything and has a passion for the pantry stated, "We are expanding the pantry and will also be offering some clothing items." #BooneImpact

Western Boone FFA has been recognized as a 2 Star Chapter by the National FFA Organization. Important Dates:
*Thursday, August 3rd, Western Boone will host 9th Grade orientation at 1:30 p.m. and 7th Grade orientation at 6:30 p.m.

*Monday, August 7th, at 6:00 p.m. the Western Boone Athletic Department will host a meeting for all parents of 6-12 grade students participating in athletics this school year.

*Tuesday, August 8th, from 5:30-7:00, Granville Wells and Thorntown Elementary Schools will host "Meet the Teacher" night.

*Wednesday, August 16th, at 6:30 p.m. Western Boone Jr. Sr. High School will host "Meet the Teacher" night.

**FIRST DAY OF SCHOOL - AUGUST 9th**

Welcome back!

post_text:
Now enrolling resident and non-resident students for our paid preschool program for the 2017-2018 school year. A $100 deposit is due to the school office by May 22, 2017, to guarantee your spot. Your child must be four by August 1, 2017. Enroll here (Preschool Only): https://goo.gl/forms/VmCC3xYKyiXgEjph2

Students who turn five on or before August 1st should enroll in Kindergarten. Enroll here (Kindergarten Only): https://goo.gl/forms/8aumpc4ZJPcMjCfg1

Please contact the school or central office if you have any questions. 765.482.6333

REMINDER: Kindergarten and Preschool round-up is today at both elementary schools. Sessions begins at 8:30 am and 1:00 pm. Documents needed:
-Copy of the Student's Birth Certificate
-Student's Immunization Records
-Proof of Residency (for students residing within our school district)
-Non-Resident Transfer Form (for students residing outside of our district) - this form will also be available at round-up.

For those south of Granville Wells in the Jamestown area, State Road 75 is still closed south of CR 500 S to 600 S so plan accordingly.

post_text: All Western Boone Schools have power and we will have school on our normal schedule today. State Road 75 is closed in front of Granville Wells between County Road 500 South and County Road 600 South due to downed poles. Granville Wells is accessible from State Road 75 and 500 South on the north end of the school. If necessary, please allow extra travel time to school if you are affected by the closure.

Community Foundation of Boone County
April 12, 2017 at 9:16 AM ¬∑

In an exciting turn of events, our Lilly Scholar Calvin Robinson accepted a full ride Beering Scholarship to Purdue. We surprised Alexis Klink and her family at Western Boone County Community School Corporation this morning with the announcement that she is now also a Lilly Scholar! Watch the video and try not to cry with excitement for this amazing young woman. #LillyScholar #BooneImpact
